<div class="tw-p-6 tw-bg-white tw-rounded tw-font-sans tw-text-gray-800 tw-space-y-8">
  <p class="tw-leading-normal">
    A <strong>stem</strong> is the intermediate form of a word between the <em>lemma</em> and its inflected surface form. It typically reflects the base pattern of a word before it’s conjugated or declined. Stemming is used in linguistic processing to group words with similar forms.
  </p>

  <div class="tw-bg-green-100 tw-border tw-border-green-300 tw-text-green-800 tw-px-4 tw-py-3 tw-rounded" role="alert">
    <p class="tw-font-semibold">ℹ️ Note:</p>
    <p class="tw-leading-normal">
      While a <strong>lemma</strong> is a dictionary entry (e.g., <span class="tw-font-mono">رَحِمَ</span>), a <strong>stem</strong> may be a simplified, reduced form (e.g., <span class="tw-font-mono">رَحْم</span>) used for grouping variants. It may not always correspond to a valid Arabic word.
    </p>

    <p class="tw-leading-normal">
      Stemming is useful for grouping words in search, clustering, or analyzing morphological variation without needing the full lemma or root system.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="tw-bg-gray-50 tw-border-l-4 tw-border-gray-300 tw-p-4">
    <p class="tw-font-semibold tw-mb-2">Example:</p>
    <ul class="tw-list-disc tw-pl-5 tw-space-y-1">
      <li>
        Lemma: <span class="tw-font-mono tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-1">رَحِمَ</span> – to have mercy
      </li>
      <li>
        Stem: <span class="tw-font-mono tw-bg-gray-100 tw-px-1">رَحْم</span>
      </li>
      <li>Related forms:
        <ul class="tw-list-disc tw-pl-5 tw-mt-1 tw-space-y-1">
          <li><span class="qpc-hafs tw-font-bold">رَحْمَة</span> (raḥmah) – mercy</li>
          <li><span class="qpc-hafs tw-font-bold">يَرْحَمُ</span> (yarḥamu) – he shows mercy</li>
          <li><span class="qpc-hafs tw-font-bold">الرَّحِيم</span> (Ar-Raḥīm) – the Merciful</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p class="tw-leading-normal">
      QUL exports stem data in the <code class="tw-font-mono">stems</code> and <code class="tw-font-mono">word_stems</code> tables of the SQLite dataset.
    </p>

